Interestingly, Jones believes that markets have already adapted to Fed policy expectations.
“In addition to the strength of the dollar and the estimated drop in inflation, there are some signs that the market has adjusted to the prospect of a more rigorous monetary policy,” Jones wrote.
Short-term interest rates have risen, the profitability curve is fairer, the spread of the credit average interest rate has expanded, and volatility has increased – all market features when the Fed tightens policy.
