On Wednesday, the government approved the "National Strategy on Immigration for the period 2015-2018" and the "Action Plan for the current year", documents considered to be "another stage that Romania is going through in efforts to modernize the immigration management process on the national territory", according to a press release.
The strategy aims to effectively manage the immigration phenomenon, including general strategic objectives, specific objectives and action directions that reflect policies established at European level, adapted to national realities.
In view of the problems faced by the states in the immediate vicinity of Romania, measures are considered for the unitary and coherent management of situations determined by the possible emergence of an influx of illegal immigrants into the territory of Romania, generated by crisis situations of a political, social, economic or military nature.
"The Romanian authorities will contribute to the creation of a flexible admission system, but at the same time they will pay special attention to citizens coming from countries with migration potential or that may affect national security," the source added.
The strategy identifies a number of factors that can influence immigration and asylum, including maintaining the conflict situation in Syria, reviving the conflict in Iraq, maintaining an unstable situation in the neighbouring areas of Romania (Ukraine, Transnistria), perpetuating and increasing the intensity of the Israeli-Palestinian armed conflict.
On the other hand, the document also sets a number of general strategic objectives related to immigration, such as: promoting legal migration, more stringent controls of the legality of the residence of third-country nationals on the territory of Romania and the appropriate application of removal and restrictive measures, the improvement of the national system.
The national strategy shall also include specific objectives relevant to the transposition and implementation of the overall strategic objectives.
These include: facilitating access on the territory of Romania to third-country nationals who respond to the needs of employment of the labour force, facilitating access of third-country nationals to higher education institutions in Romania for areas and professions identified as deficient.
Regarding the 2015 Action Plan, the Government considers it to be “a means by which concrete activities are established that lead to the creation of a flexible system for stopping the growing migration phenomenon”.
